This paper is primarily focused on analyzing the security of cellular networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the use of software-defined radio and real-time signaling, which are related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the potential for denial of service attacks, which is related to system and control theory (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
